@miimnoon thanks for raising this issue. It should have been fixed in M8, where a complete Prompt object is propagated throughout the advisor chain instead of the approach used before that was leading to metadata loss for user and system messages. Can you confirm that's the case?

From an Advisor, you now get a ChatClientRequest object instead of AdvisedRequest. You can obtain the Prompt as follows:

```
@Override
ChatClientResponse adviseCall(ChatClientRequest chatClientRequest, CallAdvisorChain callAdvisorChain) {
	Prompt prompt = chatClientRequest.prompt();
        ...
}
```
